Description: 2007 Fender Highway One StratocasterHere is a genuine American made Fender Highway One Strat! The serial number dates it to 2007. It features a Alder body, Maple neck, Rosewood fretboard with 9.5" radius. The finish is a satin nitro sunburst. It also features the Greasebucket Tone Circuit, which rolls off the highs without adding bass. Actual weight is 7 lbs 9 oz.The body is in very good condition overall with no major dings. There are a few worn areas and some light streaks are visible in the light. Nothing out of the ordinary for a lightly used guitar. No cracks, modifications or structural issues.The neck is straight and the frets show only light wear. It's in excellent playing condition with no dead frets or other major issues. The fretboard, back of the neck and headstock are clean with no dings or worn areas. No cracks, repairs or extra holes.The hardware and electronics are original and in excellent working condition. It comes with a plastic Roadrunner hardshell case which has some general wear on the outside. All of the latches, hinges and handle are in excellent working order and the interior has no bad odors.Please note that I do not set up my guitars before mailing. I have played it and everything is great as far as I'm concerned, but you may need to change the strings, adjust the action or do other maintenece to get it to your preferences.
